<span style='float: right; width: 280px; height: 187px; margin: 0 0 5px 5px; border: 1px solid black;'><script type='text/javascript'>flash_object ('http://graphics.millsberry.com/buddy/buddy_featured.swf', '280', '187', 'userName=1krista&buddyTimeStamp=20061005&buddyScriptURL=http%3A%2F%2Fmillsberry.com%2Fbuddy%2Fload_buddy_xml.phtml&unixTimeStamp=1193059651&serverTimeOffset=28800', '', 'exactfit', 'transparent');</script></span>
Meet <b>Krista</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Krista lives at <a href='/home/?user=1krista'>44368 Memorial Drive</a> in one of Metro Park's most fashionable newly renovated duplexes.  Ever since moving in on June 24, 2006, she has really enjoyed living so close to Peabody Park, because it means that she can stop by to play a quick game of soccer whenever she wants!<br><br>As you may have guessed, Krista loves soccer.  She's a very athletic young lady who spends most of her afternoons and weekends on the field at <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/peabody_park/">Peabody Park</a>, either practicing or playing in a match.  If she isn't busy dribbling the ball down the field, you can often find Krista in the stands, cheering on her favorite soccer team.  Krista says that, as much as she loves playing soccer, she loves watching it almost as much!  So, the next time you see a game in progress on the park's soccer field, keep an eye out for Krista &mdash; she'll be the one in the light blue, indigo, and silver jersey, out-maneuvering defenders and heading for the goal!<br><br>Krista doesn't spend all of her time on the soccer pitch, though!  She also enjoys games of all kinds, from arcade games to board games.  Krista often visits her best friend's house for Game Night, where they'll spend countless hours challenging each other to a wide variety of games and puzzles.  Since Krista also loves going to the pool, she was recently very excited to learn about a new game &mdash; water polo!<br><br>When Krista just wants to relax, she likes to go to her room, turn on her favorite country, classic rock, and pop CDs, and draw.  Krista says that drawing helps her to unwind after a particularly difficult soccer game.  Don't be surprised to learn, though, that most of Krista's drawings involve soccer!<br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, Krista, and congratulations for being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!<br></div>
